<br>
Finally, I disconnected my router and hub and ran the line to the machine I'm on directly. This is after literally 15 techs. The had the nerve to tell me my modem is working just fine. I'm like HELLLOOOO! IS is supposed to d/c every 15 min? I mean it has what's called a link light on it!!! No link, the light shows that! Why they insisted on shooting my PC is beyond me. If the #$%$## modem isn't connected does it really freakin matter what my setup is on the PC? <br>
<br>
Well now they're sending a tech out. Jesus. ATT @ home would have just sent me a tech without all the bullshit. I'm a PC technician by trade, troubleshooting is what I do. ATT @ home would have just sent me a tech once I explained the obvious.  Times are tight and companies are being as stingy as possible with tech support, and I realize this. But man, was I getting hot. There's nothing like being in the same mission and dying 10 times to something who's ass you were kicking, and PvP? Forget about it.<br>
<br>
